articles.original_title: James Harden questionable for the Cavaliers against the Bucks after injuring his right thumb
articles.summary: James Harden is questionable for Cleveland's game against the Milwaukee Bucks on Wednesday night because of a right thumb injury.  The Cavaliers guard was injured during Tuesday night's 109-94 win over the New York Knicks.  Harden was examined by the Cavaliers medical staff after the game and X-rays on Wednesday showed a non-displaced fracture of the distal phalanx.
